            <div type="recto">
                
                <figure>
                    <graphic url="19700908_0001r.png"/>
                    <figDesc>[Allegorical representations of Greece and France.]</figDesc>
                    <head>Les deux soeurs. </head>
                </figure>
            </div>
            <div type="verso" facs="19700908_0001v.png">
                
                <div type="message">
                    <p>H.M.V. “Cynthia” en route to Naples</p>
                    <p>Dear Lou – So far I have visited the two sisters (Marianne and Santa Lucia) and
                        have found the former to be by far the more agreeable. My machina fotografica
                        has proved of great service (cf. Illustration of international concord captured
                        at the little border town of <hi rend="underline">Cigaretta</hi>?). Was driven
                        by maniac with broken steering from Paris → Marseilles, recovered in large apt
                        filled with books + felt pens + a totally freaked out french couple (it turns
                        out they <hi rend="underline">do</hi> have freaks) Marseilles very fine, Genova
                        sucks.</p>
                    <salute>Priez d'accepter mes tres graves reservations,</salute>
                    <signed>P.</signed>
                </div>
                <div type="destination">
                    <p><stamp  type="postage">3 dr. stamp commemorating victory in 1896 Olympics of Marathon runner
                        Spyridon Louis.</stamp></p>
                    <p><stamp>Postmark illegible.</stamp></p>
                    <p><address><addrLine>M. Lourd Bernard </addrLine><addrLine>Balliol Collage Oxford,</addrLine><addrLine> U.K. INGLETERRE</addrLine><addrLine> ή Мεγάλη Βρεταννια</addrLine><addrLine>
             AIR MAIL</addrLine></address></p>
                </div>
            </div>
            
